{% # Validation - Block - Embed v2.0.1 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.0.1 — drop the display-width cap so embeds fill the content track full-width like production (the cap re-introduced the display compression the harness model deliberately removed; the small + centered look was a harness artifact, not embed's real rendering). Page is taller; loading=lazy bounds the iframe network cost. content_width case now asserts painted geometry. Keep the inside-block label exception (overflow: hidden).
  - v2.0.0 — token-section is now the real production theme-root grid (drop the `display: block` override + the `.block-validation-suite` flex wrapper + the local outline/label CSS). Blocks render as direct children; harness chrome + the layout-neutral outline/label indicator come from `validation--harness-styles`. Per `validation.md` § Harness layout.
  - v1.0.0 — initial

  Block-validation harness for `embed`. The JSON template at
  `templates/index.validation--primitive--embed.json` bakes the test
  matrix; the section renders the blocks directly as children of the
  theme-root grid, labelled via `validation--block-labels`.

  Diagnostic intent:
  1. The URL parser resolves each supported provider URL shape (YouTube
     watch / short / shorts / embed; Vimeo public / unlisted / player) to
     the right embed src + emits the matching `provider:*` modifier.
  2. Blank or unparseable URLs fall through to the placeholder branch
     (`placeholder_svg_tag`); an unparseable URL additionally emits the
     editor-only `.diagnostic` (hidden outside `shopify-design-mode`).
  3. media_size wires the `sizing:*` modifier + aspect-ratio; content_width
     caps; top-spacing applies per breakpoint.

  Reachable only at /?view=validation--primitive--embed.
  See `.context/docs/validation.md`.
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign max_inline_size = section.settings.max_inline_size
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root">
  {% render 'validation--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class="validation__intro">
    <h1>Block: embed</h1>
    <p>
      Matrix in
      <code>templates/index.validation--primitive--embed.json</code>. Each entry exercises one URL shape the parser
      recognizes (YouTube watch / short / shorts / embed; Vimeo public / unlisted / player), plus the placeholder branch
      (blank + unparseable), a media_size aspect-ratio, a content_width cap, and top-spacing. The
      <code>data-modifiers</code> attribute surfaces the resolved provider + sizing. Embeds render full-width (live
      third-party iframes; the page is long — they lazy-load).
    </p>
  </header>

  {% if section.blocks.size > 0 %}
    {% content_for 'blocks' %}

    {% render 'validation--block-labels', section: section %}
  {% else %}
    <p class="validation__empty">No blocks declared in the template.</p>
  {% endif %}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  {% if max_inline_size and max_inline_size != blank %}
    --max-inline-size: {{ max_inline_size }}px;
  {% endif %}
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
{% render 'validation--harness-styles' %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Block: embed",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--validation--primitive--embed",
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@theme" }],
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "max_inline_size",
      "label": "Max width",
      "min": 800,
      "max": 1920,
      "step": 20,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 1280
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

{% stylesheet %}
  @layer components {
    /* Embed is `overflow: hidden`, which clips the shared above-the-block label;
       place it inside the top-left corner instead. The doubled section class
       lifts specificity over the shared label rule — embeds without a provider /
       sizing modifier carry no [data-modifiers], so media's [data-modifiers]
       bump can't be reused here. */
    .shopify-section.shopify-section--validation--primitive--embed token-section > .shopify-block--embed::before {
      inset-block-start: 0.5rem;
      inset-block-end: auto;
      inset-inline-start: 0.5rem;
      z-index: 1;
      /* Backing chip — the label sits over live video thumbnails, so foreground
         text alone washes out. */
      padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem;
      border-radius: 0.25rem;
      background-color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.85);
      color: #1a1a1a;
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}
